library(tree)
cat('Classification Tree for social_ads 0925 ')
## Classification Tree for social_ads 0925
social_Ads <- read.csv('./Assignment/Ads.csv')
attach(social_Ads)
Purchased.code <- as.character(social_Ads$Purchased)
Purchased.code[Purchased.code=="1"]="No"
Purchased.code[Purchased.code=="0"]="Yes"
social_Ads <- data.frame(social_Ads,Purchased.code)
new_social_Ads <- social_Ads[,c(-1,-2,-6)]
dim(new_social_Ads)
## [1] 400   7
#head(new_social_Ads)
tree_model_socail_Ads <- tree(Purchased.code~.,new_social_Ads)
plot(tree_model_socail_Ads)
text(tree_model_socail_Ads,pretty = 0)

#Test the model accuracy
summary(tree_model_socail_Ads)
## 
## Classification tree:
## tree(formula = Purchased.code ~ ., data = new_social_Ads)
## Variables actually used in tree construction:
## [1] "Age"             "EstimatedSalary" "Eduction"        "occupation"     
## Number of terminal nodes:  12 
## Residual mean deviance:  0.3044 = 118.1 / 388 
## Misclassification error rate: 0.08 = 32 / 400
#Fit a Classification Tree for training data set
set.seed(2)
train <- sample(1:nrow(new_social_Ads),200)
test  <- new_social_Ads [-train,]
tree_new_social_Ads_train <- tree(Purchased.code~.,new_social_Ads,subset=train)
plot(tree_new_social_Ads_train)
text(tree_new_social_Ads_train,pretty=0)

#Test the model accuracy(train model with test data set)
tree_predicted <- predict(tree_new_social_Ads_train,test,type="class")
Purchased_code_test <- Purchased.code[-train]
table(tree_predicted,Purchased_code_test)
##               Purchased_code_test
## tree_predicted  No Yes
##            No   71  16
##            Yes   9 104
m <- table(tree_predicted,Purchased_code_test)
misrate <- ((m[1,2]+m[2,1])/sum(m))
paste("Misclassification error rate is ",misrate) #Misclassification error rate is considerable.
## [1] "Misclassification error rate is  0.125"
#Construct the Cross validation plot
set.seed(3)
cv_new_social_Ads <- cv.tree(tree_new_social_Ads_train,FUN=prune.misclass)
names(cv_new_social_Ads)
## [1] "size"   "dev"    "k"      "method"
cv_new_social_Ads
## $size
## [1] 10  3  2  1
## 
## $dev
## [1] 17 15 24 63
## 
## $k
## [1] -Inf    0   11   42
## 
## $method
## [1] "misclass"
## 
## attr(,"class")
## [1] "prune"         "tree.sequence"
plot(cv_new_social_Ads$size, cv_new_social_Ads$dev, type = "b")

#Select the best size of the tree model
#According the plot in part 3.8 above, best size of the tree model is 3.
#Obtain the best classification tree by pruning
pruned_new_social_Ads <- prune.misclass(tree_new_social_Ads_train,best=3)
pruned_new_social_Ads
## node), split, n, deviance, yval, (yprob)
##       * denotes terminal node
## 
## 1) root 200 249.20 Yes ( 0.31500 0.68500 )  
##   2) Age < 43.5 148 101.40 Yes ( 0.10811 0.89189 )  
##     4) EstimatedSalary < 90500 131  20.70 Yes ( 0.01527 0.98473 ) *
##     5) EstimatedSalary > 90500 17  15.84 No ( 0.82353 0.17647 ) *
##   3) Age > 43.5 52  32.92 No ( 0.90385 0.09615 ) *
plot(pruned_new_social_Ads)
text(pruned_new_social_Ads,pretty=0)

#Test the model accuracy for pruned
tree_predict <- predict(pruned_new_social_Ads,test,type="class")
Purchased_code_test <- Purchased.code[-train]
table(tree_predicted,Purchased_code_test)
##               Purchased_code_test
## tree_predicted  No Yes
##            No   71  16
##            Yes   9 104
m2 <- table(tree_predicted,Purchased_code_test)
mis_rate <-((m2[1,2]+m2[2,1])/sum(m2))
paste("Misclassification error rate is ",mis_rate)
## [1] "Misclassification error rate is  0.125"
# Misclassification rate of the pruned tree model is lower than that of the unpruned tree, indicating that
# pruning has improved the performance.
